create(bytes32,address,bytes,bytes,bytes.details: The Vault can only be deployed once. Therefore, this function is permissioned to ensure that it is deployed to the right address.

params.salt: Salt used to create the Vault. See `getDeploymentAddress`.
params.targetAddress: Expected Vault address. The function will revert if the given salt does not deploy the Vault to the target address.

params.selector: The 4-byte selector of the permissioned function

getActionId(bytes4).notice: Returns the action identifier associated with the external function described by `selector`.

getDeploymentAddress(bytes32).notice: Gets deployment address for a given salt.

documentation.text:
@notice Emitted when the Vault is deployed.
 @param vault The Vault's address
@notice The given salt does not match the generated address when attempting to create the Vault.
@notice The bytecode for the given contract does not match the expected bytecode.
@notice Gets deployment address for a given salt.
@notice One-off factory to deploy the Vault at a specific address.
